<p> <b>EXPERIENCE</b>


<h3>Massachusetts College of Art and Design</h3> 
    <h4>Orientation Graphic Designer</h4> June 2018 to August 

<p>Hired by MassArt Student development via competitive interviewing, currently designing Orientation themed branding for MassArt’s Fall 2018 Student Orientation: Including invitation cards, t-shirts, and calendars.</p>

<h3>Todd Architects LTD</h3> <h4>Graphic Design Intern</h4> June 2018

<p>Fulfilling presentation and modeling design needs, while working on redesigning project sheets and their InDesign template for use in the future by Todd Architects marketing.</p>

<h3>Bob Jones University Collegian</h3> Staff Designer,
Academic Year 2016-2017

<p>Designed infographics, page layouts, and
advertisements for the Bob Jones University
student run newspaper. Worked with staff
writers, photographers, and editors in order to
    create the school’s weekly newspaper.</p>

<h3>Arrowstreet Inc</h3> <h4>Design Intern</h4> Summer 2016

<p>Worked with the Arrowstreet Graphic Design
Department on Towson Town Center modeling,
and gained experience in sustainable design.
Completed a sustainable design project evaluating
    one of Arrowstreet’s current projects.</p>

<h3>YouthBuild Boston</h3> <h4>Intern Designer</h4> Summer 2015

<p>Working on design solutions and projects, creating
floor plans and drawings Interns visited
construction sites, design firms and museums. The
internship finished with a landscape architecture
    project for Washington Gateway Main Street.</p>


<b>OTHER EXPERIENCE</b>

<h3>Isabella Stewart Gardner Museum</h3> <h4>Gallery Officer</h4>
December 2017- present
<p>Responsible for the protection of the collection,
and safety of staff and visitors. Responsibilities
include responding to guests in a courteous manner,
patrolling galleries, and presenting a professional
image to the public.</p>
